CommonFields.Title: Nanocomposites of Ferroelectric Polymers with TiO2 Nanoparticles Exhibiting Significantly Enhanced Electrical Energy Density
Author: Li, Junjun
Seok, Sang Il
Chu, Baojin
Dogan, Fatih
Zhang, Qiming
Wang, Qing
CommonFields.Location: Department of Materials Science and Engineering The Pennsylvania State University University Park, Pennsylvania 16802, USA

MolecularWeight.description: The absolute weight-average molecular weight of the polymer, determined by gel permeation chromatography (GPC) equipped with light scattering detectors in DMF, is ~240 kDa

Matrix.Description: synthesized via a copolymerization of vinylidene fluoride (VDF) and chlorotrifluoroethylene (CTFE) and a subsequent dechlorination reaction

Width.description: The TiO2 nanoparticles with a rod-shaped dimension (~20 nm ~ 70 nm)

Length.description: The TiO2 nanoparticles with a rod-shaped dimension (~20 nm ~ 70 nm)

Depth.description: The TiO2 nanoparticles with a rod-shaped dimension (~20 nm ~ 70 nm)

Heating.Description: The surfaces of the TiO2 nanoparticles were then modified by refluxing in aqueous CO2-free barium hydroxide solution for 2 h under Ar atmosphere

Mixing.Description: Thin films of the nanocomposites were fabricated by casting DMF solution of the TiO2 nanoparticles and P(VDF-TrFE-CTFE) followed by drying at 120 °C for 8 h in vacuo.

MoldingInfo.Description: The film was further melt-pressed at 160 °C under 3000 psi to remove voids and residual solvent.

Dielectric_Real_Permittivity.description: measured at 1 kHz and room temperature with a 1 V bias

Dielectric_Loss_Tangent.description: measured at 1 kHz and room temperature with a 1 V bias
